## 5. 📒 Generation Ledger / History

**Current state:** No persistence. Generated designs disappear on refresh.

**What to build:**

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Storage | PostgreSQL table or Medusa custom entity |
| Record per generation | `id`, `customer_id`, `prompt`, `occasion`, `style`, `flavor`, `zodiac_sign`, `provider`, `model`, `status`, `image_urls[]`, `image_count`, `credit_cost`, `created_at`, `completed_at`, `failed_reason` |
| User history API | `GET /api/ai-cake-studio/history` — paginated list of past generations |
| Design detail API | `GET /api/ai-cake-studio/designs/{id}` — single design with images |
| Saved/favorited designs | Allow user to "save" a design for later |
| Admin view | List all generations with filters (for cost monitoring) |

**Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE ai_generations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  customer_id VARCHAR NOT NULL,
  prompt TEXT NOT NULL,
  occasion VARCHAR(50),
  style VARCHAR(50),
  flavor VARCHAR(50),
  zodiac_sign VARCHAR(20),
  provider VARCHAR(30) NOT NULL,         -- 'openai', 'stability'
  provider_model VARCHAR(50),            -- 'dall-e-3', 'sdxl'
  status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',  -- pending, completed, failed
  image_urls JSONB DEFAULT '[]',
  image_count INT DEFAULT 0,
  credit_cost INT DEFAULT 1,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  failed_reason TEXT,
  metadata JSONB DEFAULT '{}'
);

CREATE INDEX idx_generations_customer ON ai_generations(customer_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_generations_status ON ai_generations(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_generations_created ON ai_generations(created_at DESC);
```

